videos.description: Dakota Allen picks off Kyle Allen leading to a Texas Tech field goal early in the first quarter.

videos.description: Nic Shimonek extends the Texas Tech lead with a short 20-yard pass touchdown to Justin Stockton.
videos.headline: Stockton scores on a screen from 20 yards out

videos.description: Vaughnte Dorsey takes a knee to his head on a kick return and has to be carted off the field. He gives a thumbs up to the fans as he exits.
videos.headline: Dorsey leaves game with neck injury

videos.description: Back-up QB Kyle Postma comes into the game and takes it in for the touchdown on 4th and 1 to Houston within 10.
videos.headline: Postma breaks a few tackles on 4th down for Houston TD

videos.description: Kyle Postma rolls out and finds Linell Bonner for a four-yard touchdown with 15 seconds remaining.
videos.headline: Postma connects with Bonner for late Houston TD

videos.description: Texas Tech head coach Kilff Kingsbury liked what he saw from his fifth-year QB despite the offense's sloppy play.
videos.headline: Kingsbury: Shimonek showed mental toughness
